title.narrative: COMMUNICATION, ADVOCACY AND PARTNERSHIPS

description.narrative: UNICEF's voice and public engagement significantly enhanced, particularly with GRN and key partners, which contributes to Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Private Sector Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2023, government institutions at the national and regional level are routinely reporting on the realization of the rights of all children and adolescents .

description.narrative: COVID-19 continues to disrupt normal programme implementation, resulting in a shift from in-person support to distance and remote delivery – which has made digital development integral to how UNICEF Namibia works upstream and in the field. The CO continues to redefine its role in responding and repositioning itself in upstream advocacy to leverage resources for children and influence decisions. With this repositioning, UNICEF is incorporating innovative strategies that;resulted in policy review to ensure continued schooling and routine immunisation during emergencies. Key messages on access to clean water and sanitation as key to combating COVID-19 were distributed. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/12/2021
